US Defense Secretary Robert Gates declared the US mission in Iraq was in its "endgame."
During President George W. Bush's farewell visit, a journalist threw shoes at him, symbolizing lingering hostility.
Despite signing a security pact with Iraqi Prime Minister Nouri al-Maliki, Bush admitted more work remained.
The shoe-throwing incident, while chaotic, highlighted the mixed sentiments towards Bush's actions in Iraq.
Bush, unfazed, joked about the shoe size and downplayed the event.
This unexpected farewell gesture underscored the complexities and divisions surrounding the Iraq war as Bush's presidency neared its end.
